                            <comment id="15056541" author="stephanewen" created="Mon, 14 Dec 2015 19:29:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The class is not really designed for concurrent use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I see your point, it is actually inconsistent with the fact that the &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; methods use the lock.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would actually suggest to not use a lock in the &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; methods either. In a single threaded use, there is really no need for these locks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
